    "description": "Canonical BRMSTE domain fleet across all five cloud lanes (Cloudflare edge, Hetzner origins, AWS industrial edge, Azure, Siemens Industrial Edge Management). Known apexes are hand-maintained; the full active zone list (expected_total) is synced from Cloudflare via scripts/sync-cf-zones-to-manifest.sh into domains/manifest.json. Audited credential-free by scripts/polish-domains.sh against policy.required_headers / policy.forbidden_headers.",
    "serving_layer": "As of 2026-07-18 the live fleet is served by the Hetzner 'domains-platform' (Caddy, x-brmste-platform=domains-platform, template brmste-unified-v1, x-brmste-origin=hetzner) fronted by Cloudflare. The coming-soon Worker brmste-com-coming-soon remains the legacy/fallback surface. Security headers are therefore set at the Caddy/domains-platform layer, not (only) the Worker — policy below is the uniform target for whichever layer answers.",
    "doctrine": "OPERATOR DOESNT BASH · CURSOR NEVER SIGNS · EDGE SIGNS · JUDGMENT SIGNS",
    "generated_at": "2026-07-18T19:00:00Z"
